  "text": "<html>\r\n    <head>\r\n    <style>\r\n        .unselectable {\r\n          -webkit-user-select: none;\r\n          -webkit-touch-callout: none;\r\n          -moz-user-select: none;\r\n          -ms-user-select: none;\r\n          user-select: none;\r\n        }\r\n      <\/style>\r\n      <\/head>\r\n\r\n<body class=\"unselectable\">\r\n \r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">INTERNATIONAL ORGANIZATIONS<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">OPEC<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">OPEC means the Organization of Petroleum Exporting Countries.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">OPEC was initially formed in September 1960 by the following countries Saudi Arabia, Venezuela, Iraq, Iran, and Kuwait.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Then after a while some other countries joined which includes; Qatar, Libya, Indonesia, Abu, Dhabi, Algeria, Nigeria, Ecuador and Gabon joined the organization.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The major objective of OPEC is to devise ways and means of ensuring the stabilization of prices in international oil markets with a view to eliminating harmful and unnecessary<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">OAU<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The Organization of African Unity was formed on May 25, 1963 in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia under the chairmanship of Emperor Haile Sellasia of Ethiopia. The OAU was founded on the principles of respect and the recognition of the sovereignty, equality and territorial integrity of member states and non-interference in the internal affairs of member states.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Organs of OAU&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">1. Assembly of Heads of States and Government&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">2. Council of Ministers&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">3. General Secretariat&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">4. Commission of Mediation, Conciliation and Arbitration<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The OAU was formed for the promotion of African States&rsquo; unity and solidarity; the defence of sovereignty, independence and territorial integrity of African states as well as the advancement of Africa economic welfare.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">UNO<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The UNO charter of 1945 aims at ensuring world peace and security and to take a collective measure for the prevention and removal of threats to the peace.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The UNO charter aims at____.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. ensuring economic equality among nations<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. protecting the right of refugees<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. ensuring world peace and security<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. ensuring fair treatment for prisoners of war<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C (2018\/2019, no 3).<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The United Nations charter is an instrument that____.<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. sets out the rights and obligations of member states. B. provides for funding of member states<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. facilitates the resolution of disputes among member states. D. determines the admission of member states<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C (2018\/2019, no 4).&nbsp;<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">United Nations charter is an instrument that facilitates the resolution of disputes among member states<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Example<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The five permanent members of the United Nations Security Council are<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A. China, U.K, U.S.S.R, U.S.A. and France<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">B. U.S.S.R, Germany., Canada., India and China<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">C. U.K, France, U.S.A, Brazil and Ethiopia<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">D. U.S.A, China. Liberia, U.S.S.R and Italy<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">A (2012\/2013, no 12).<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">China, U.K, U.S.S.R, U.S.A. and France<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><strong><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">Commonwealth of Nations<\/span><\/strong><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">The Commonwealth of Nations is a voluntary association of independent states most of which were once colonized by the United Kingdom and are former colonies. The Commonwealth is a successor of the British Empire in 1884. It is made up of 53 member states with headquarters at Marlborough House, London. The founding members of Commonwealth of Nations were United Kingdom, Australia, New Zealand, Canada, and South Africa.&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:8pt; line-height:108%; font-size:12pt;\"><span style=\"font-family:'Times New Roman';\">&nbsp;<\/span><\/p>\r\n \r\n<\/body>\r\n\r\n<\/html>",
  "chapIndex": "INTERNATIONAL ORGANIZATIONS"
}